Session 1 ‚Äì Network Defense & Countermeasures
BASIC MCQs (1‚Äì10)
1. Information Security primarily aims to protect which three core principles?
A. Authentication, Authorization, Accounting
B. Confidentiality, Integrity, Availability
C. Privacy, Performance, Scalability
D. Encryption, Hashing, Digital Signature

2. Which of the following best defines Information Security?
A. Protecting hardware from physical damage
B. Protecting information from unauthorized access, use, disclosure, disruption, modification, or destruction
C. Protecting networks only from hackers
D. Protecting software using antivirus

3. Why is Information Security important for organizations?
A. To reduce hardware cost
B. To improve employee productivity
C. To protect business assets and maintain trust
D. To increase internet speed

4. Which factor directly contributes to financial losses due to poor security?
A. Network latency
B. Data breaches and downtime
C. CPU utilization
D. Software updates

5. From a security perspective, increasing internet users globally mainly results in:
A. Reduced attack surface
B. Increased vulnerability exposure
C. Lower cybercrime
D. Elimination of malware

6. A vulnerability is best described as:
A. A potential attacker
B. A weakness that can be exploited
C. An actual attack
D. A security policy

7. Which of the following is an example of a threat?
A. Unpatched operating system
B. SQL Injection attack
C. Weak password policy
D. Open port

8. Risk in Information Security is a function of:
A. Vulnerability √ó Threat
B. Threat √ó Asset value
C. Vulnerability √ó Threat √ó Impact
D. Impact √ó Likelihood only

9. QoS (Quality of Service) in networking mainly focuses on:
A. Encrypting data
B. Improving application performance
C. Managing traffic to meet service requirements
D. Preventing malware attacks

10. Which QoS parameter represents the variation in packet delay?
A. Latency
B. Throughput
C. Jitter
D. Bandwidth

INTERMEDIATE MCQs (11‚Äì20)
11. Which security principle is violated when unauthorized modification of data occurs?
A. Confidentiality
B. Integrity
C. Availability
D. Non-repudiation

12. The money factor in Information Security mainly refers to:
A. Cost of internet services
B. Cost of hardware procurement
C. Financial impact of breaches and security controls
D. Employee salary costs

13. According to OWASP statistics, which category frequently ranks highest in web vulnerabilities?
A. Security Misconfiguration
B. Broken Access Control
C. Injection Flaws
D. Cryptographic Failures

14. Which of the following best represents risk management?
A. Eliminating all vulnerabilities
B. Ignoring low-impact threats
C. Identifying, assessing, and mitigating risks
D. Deploying antivirus only

15. OpenVAS is primarily used for:
A. Packet sniffing
B. Vulnerability assessment
C. Traffic shaping
D. Firewall configuration

16. Which vulnerability type is most likely exploited by ransomware?
A. Physical vulnerability
B. Human vulnerability
C. Software vulnerability
D. Environmental vulnerability

17. From a security viewpoint, high internet penetration leads to:
A. Reduced malware spread
B. Larger attack surface
C. Lower phishing attempts
D. Better confidentiality

18. Which QoS metric indicates the maximum data rate of a network path?
A. Latency
B. Jitter
C. Bandwidth
D. Packet loss

19. Wireshark is best categorized as a:
A. Intrusion Detection System
B. Vulnerability scanner
C. Packet analyzer
D. Firewall

20. Which scenario represents availability compromise?
A. Data theft
B. Website defacement
C. Denial of Service attack
D. Password cracking

ADVANCED MCQs (21‚Äì30)
21. An organization with valuable customer data but weak access controls faces high risk because:
A. Threat probability is low
B. Vulnerability and asset value are high
C. Impact is negligible
D. Only internal users exist

22. If vulnerability exists but no threat is present, the risk is:
A. Maximum
B. Moderate
C. Zero or negligible
D. Unacceptable

23. OWASP Top 10 is most useful for:
A. Network performance tuning
B. Secure software development guidance
C. Hardware hardening
D. Antivirus selection

24. Which attack most directly exploits poor QoS handling?
A. SQL Injection
B. Buffer Overflow
C. DDoS
D. Cross-Site Scripting

25. During a vulnerability scan, OpenVAS reporting high CVSS score indicates:
A. Low risk vulnerability
B. False positive
C. High severity vulnerability
D. Network congestion

26. In risk calculation, impact is best defined as:
A. Frequency of attacks
B. Potential damage caused by exploitation
C. Number of vulnerabilities
D. Number of attackers

27. Which Wireshark metric is most relevant to evaluate VoIP quality?
A. Packet size
B. Jitter
C. MAC address
D. TTL value

28. From a business perspective, why is preventive security often preferred over reactive security?
A. Easier to implement
B. Lower long-term cost
C. Requires less expertise
D. Eliminates all threats

29. A misconfigured firewall rule allowing unnecessary inbound traffic represents:
A. Threat
B. Risk
C. Vulnerability
D. Impact

30. Which statement best reflects CDAC‚Äôs security philosophy?
A. Security is a one-time setup
B. Security is purely technical
C. Security is a continuous risk management process
D. Security eliminates all attacks

